								<div class="title" id="post-title-4041545">
																		Black As Night: Part 1
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3075960&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204537" alt="stormbreath" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3075960)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stormbreath" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3075960); return false;" >stormbreath</a></span> <span class="odate time_1540679358 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Oct 2018 22:29</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4041545">
									

<p>This is the new Part 1 of Black as Night, a series I'm working on about Mr. Night, the end of the Chicago Spirit and the rise of the Chicago Spectre. Part 2 and the Hub will be coming soon, but in the meantime you can skip to <a href="/uiu-file-1941-016">Part 3</a>, which has been up for some time.</p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li><strong>The tale can only have one survivor; how you define that is up to you.</strong></li>
<li><strong>One of the characters has to end up in a costume, against their will, to solve some issue that comes up in the tale.</strong></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>The one survivor is, of course, Night. Night ends up in a ghost costume to act the part of a sycophant to Robinson/Bones/Flannagan/Schulz, in the Tommy costume to pretend to not be himself, and a Schulz costume to answer the door. He doesn't really want to be in any of those.</p>
<p>Big thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1553042&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1550722431" alt="PeppersGhost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1553042)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;">PeppersGhost</a></span> for talking about Mr. Night (who is his character) on IRC over six months ago. Most of what was discussed on that didn't end up making it into this tale (to say this is drastically different from how I first imagined the Part 1 of Black as Night is a massive understatement), but there are elements that influenced the tale, as well as the later entries in this series.</p>
<p>Another big thanks goes to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3938622&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1550722431" alt="The Great Hippo" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3938622)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/the-great-hippo" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938622); return false;">The Great Hippo</a></span>, who gave me some really good crit that lead to a large rewrite of the tale, and strengthened it a lot. The feedback they gave was really good, and this would have been a lot worse without it.</p>
<p>And finally, thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stallmantic" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3472766); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3472766&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1550722431" alt="Stallmantic" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3472766)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stallmantic" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3472766); return false;">Stallmantic</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kindlyturtleclem" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4504036); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4504036&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1550722431" alt="KindlyTurtleClem" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4504036)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kindlyturtleclem" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4504036); return false;">KindlyTurtleClem</a></span> for looking at this as well.</p>
Slang definitions:<br />
<dl>
<dt><strong>Cheesers:</strong></dt>
<dd>The SCP Foundation<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-6381-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-6381-1')">1</a></sup></dd>
<dt><strong>Trick:</strong></dt>
<dd>An anomalous action, magic spell, whatever</dd>
<dt><strong>Wand:</strong></dt>
<dd>An anomalous item/tool</dd>
</dl>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-6381-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-6381-1')">1</a>. Fun fact about this: Nobody knows what it means or where it came from! I'm not talking in-universe here, by the way! I don't remember who suggested it to me, nobody it could've been says they did it, and it's so bizarre to have no inherent meaning! Now that's what I call a creepypasta.</div>
</div>

